text:
34 and 32 Roosevelt Street, adjoining and north of the N.E. corner of New Bowery. Both of these structures project thru this triangular site to the latter thoroughfare. No. 32 is building with fire escape and No. 34 is building with the plumbing fixtures in the window. Name on window is T. Laro. There is a notice to use entrance at 32 Bowery. The name in telephone book, Winter 1939-40, is Theo Laro, plumbing contractor, 32 New Bowery.

February 22, 1940

Gift of Beecher Ogden
title: Manhattan: Roosevelt Street - New Bowery
